Initialize MACRO Tile Parameters for MacroTile

This is used to generate a list of parameters for MacroTile and should be used during its initialization. MACRO.Tile.Parameters will generate parameters that are passed to the initialize method of the component objects in a tile:

  • HumanPop: creates parameters by calling {link{HumanPop.Parameters}

  • MacroPatch: creates parameters by calling MACRO.Patch.Parameters

  • MacroMosquitoPop: directly initializes parameters

MACRO.Tile.Parameters(N = 10, patchSize = 20, patchMin = 10,
  aquaModel = "emerge", aquaPars = list(lambda = rep(10, 10)))

Arguments

N

number of patches
patchSize

passed to sitePops
patchMin

passed to sitePops
aquaModel

character in 'Emerge', 'EL4P
aquaPars

Aquatic Ecology module specific parameters (see MACRO.Patch.Parameters for details)

  • Emerge: list with elements 'lambda'

  • EL4P: list with elements

Value

return a list
